      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must closely replicate VAD operating envelope including blood analog rheology and pump geometry at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used water-glycerol blood analog rather than porcine blood; rotational speed range covers only 3 of 5 COU operating points. Significant test condition gaps remain."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of predicted vs. measured hemolysis index with statistical metrics and uncertainty overlap analysis required at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index comparison performed with mean absolute error reported; however no confidence interval overlap analysis is provided and systematic bias is unaddressed."
    },
